</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.SC.1A-2-2" type="ext"/>[SCR Pt 1A.2.2] </edpnum><title>Applications in vacation times</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>It can occur that proceedings have to be brought before the court even in the fixed vacation period. The court arranges for particular judges to be designated as &quot;duty&quot; judges in that period. The procedure for obtaining a vacation hearing of proceedings in the Court of Appeal is dealt with in 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.R52" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">UCPR r 51.57</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT1A.R3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[SCR Pt 1A r 3] r 3 Court Holiday">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="true" ln.user-displayed="false">(Repealed)</leg:levelstatus></leg:levelinfo>
